<page>
    <shortlink>ux list clientside event onswipe</shortlink>
    <topic>onSwipe Event</topic>
    <description>Fires when the user swipes (left, right, up or down) on a row in the List.</description>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>ele</name>
            <type>object</type>
            <description>The element that contains the data.</description>
        </argument>
        <argument>
            <name>data</name>
            <type>object</type>
            <description>The data for the row.</description>
        </argument>
        <argument>
            <name>e</name>
            <type>object</type>
            <description>An object that contains the following properties:</description>
            <properties>
                <property>
                    <name>swipeDirection</name>
                    <type>string</type>
                    <description>The direction that the user swips (left, right, up, down.)</description>
                </property>
                <property>
                    <name>rowNumber</name>
                    <type>number</type>
                    <description>A zero-based row number that the user swipd.</description>
                </property>
            </properties>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <discussion>
        <p>In addition the Javascript can reference the 'this' scope, a pointer to the List object.</p>
    </discussion>
